Former president Jacob Zuma has penned a scathing letter to president Cyril Ramaphosa. He's questioning Ramaphosa's commitment to fighting corruption. eNCA Political Editor Vuyo Mvoko has more details. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Former President Jacob Zuma has issued a scathing letter addressed to current President Cyril Ramaphosa, challenging his leadership. Zuma focuses his letter on how Ramaphosa is allegedly not genuine to the true character of the ANC. This letter's release comes as the ruling party gets into day one of its National Executive Committee meeting. READ: Ramaphosa: ANC should disassociate itself from anyone accused of corruption The former president has taken issue with Ramaphosa for calling the African National Congress 'accused number 1'. Zuma challenges Ramaphosa to come clean about financial donations for the campaign that won him the ANC presidency in 2017, better known as CR17. Read the full letter below. Courtesy #DStv403 JGZ Letter to CR by eNCA.com on Scribd 